This method sets the marketplace contract address for super admin validations.
This method is called for the first time when the marketplace contract is created, and 
can be called again but only by the super admin itself.
@param _contractAddress - The address of the deployed marketplace contract.

addNftToSingleNftsArray(address,uint256).notice: This method adds an NFT to the single NFTs array. This method is called whenever is removed from a collection and is to be listed as an individual array.

constructor.notice: ERC721 constructor is called with the provided token name and symbol.

createNft(string,uint256,string,address,.notice: This method mints an nft, increments the nftCount accordingly, generates a new nftID for it,  and adds it as an independent nft by default.

deleteNft(address,uint256).notice: This method burns an nft, decrements the nft count and removes it from the idToIndex mapping.

getAllSingleNftsByOwnerAddress(address).notice: This method returns a list of all the nfts owned by the provided address.

getListedSingleNftIds().notice: This method returns an array of all the listed single NFTs.

getNftByTokenId(uint256).notice: This method returns the NFT according to the provided nftId.

getOwnerByNftId(uint256).notice: This method fetches the address of the seller of the respective NFT.

isListedSingleNftorNot(uint256).notice: This function checks whether an nft belongs to single nfts array and is listed or not.

listNft(address,uint256).notice: This method sets the value of isListed parameter for the given nftId to be true.

removeNftFromSingleNftsArray(address,uin.notice: This method removes an nft from the singleNfts array. It is called whenever an nft is added to a collection.

setMarketplaceContractAddress(address).notice: This method sets the marketplace contract address for super admin validations. This method is called for the first time when the marketplace contract is created, and  can be called again but only by the super admin itself.

setSold(uint256,address).notice: This method sets the value of isSold parameter for the given nftId to be true.

setUnsold(uint256).notice: This methods sets the isSold parameter of the provided nftId to be false. It is called when the newOwner again wants to sell the NFT.

tokenURI(uint256).notice: This function overrides the tokenURI function of ERC721URIStorage contract. It is necessary to be overriden in order to set the token URI of an NFT.

unlistNft(address,uint256).notice: This method sets the value of isListed parameter for the given nftId to be false.

updatePrice(address,uint256,uint256).notice: This method updates the price of the provided _nftId with the new price.

userdoc.notice: This contract mints and stores the NFTS with their necesary details in a struct defined  in the Definitions contract, and provides all the necessary methods for manipulating the same.
